# Livshistorier(The Audio Time Capsule)

The Insight: You are already building "Voice" and "Interleaved Feeds." 
You are also targeting families with rich migration histories(Bosnia / Turkey to Denmark).
Those stories are at risk of being lost.

## The Unicorn Feature: Turn the "Weekly Question" into an Audio Biography.

How it works:

The Prompt: Instead of "How are you?", ask "Hvordan mødte du Far?"(How did you meet Dad ?) or "Fortæl om din ankomst til Danmark"(Tell us about arriving in Denmark).

The Output: The senior records a voice answer.
This is saved not just to the feed, but to a permanent "Livsbog"(Life Book) in the app.

Why it's a Unicorn: It transforms the app from a "burden manager" (meds/pain) into a "Family Heirloom." It gives the senior a role as the Storyteller, preserving dignity and legacy.

## Feature 2: Livshistorier(The Heirloom)
You mentioned cost is a concern for Voice.
Good news: Raw Audio is cheap.The expensive part is AI Transcription.
We will skip transcription for now and just capture the voice itself.

1. The "Recorder Widget" We replace the text input in WeeklyQuestion with this simple recorder.

Create src / features / memories / AudioRecorder.jsx:

JavaScript

import React, { useState, useRef } from 'react';
import { Mic, Square, Play } from 'lucide-react';

export const AudioRecorder = ({ onRecordingComplete }) => {
    const [isRecording, setIsRecording] = useState(false);
    const [audioUrl, setAudioUrl] = useState(null);
    const mediaRecorderRef = useRef(null);
    const chunksRef = useRef([]);

    const startRecording = async () => {
        const stream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ audio: true });
        mediaRecorderRef.current = new MediaRecorder(stream);

        mediaRecorderRef.current.ondataavailable = (e) => {
            if (e.data.size > 0) chunksRef.current.push(e.data);
        };

        mediaRecorderRef.current.onstop = () => {
            const blob = new Blob(chunksRef.current, { type: 'audio/webm' });
            const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
            setAudioUrl(url);
            onRecordingComplete(blob); // Send blob up to parent to upload to Firebase Storage
            chunksRef.current = [];
        };

        mediaRecorderRef.current.start();
        setIsRecording(true);
    };

    const stopRecording = () => {
        mediaRecorderRef.current.stop();
        setIsRecording(false);
    };

    return (
        <div className= "flex flex-col items-center gap-4 p-6 bg-stone-50 rounded-3xl border-2 border-dashed border-stone-200" >
        {!audioUrl ? (
            <button
                    onClick= { isRecording? stopRecording: startRecording }
                    className = {`
                        w-20 h-20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center transition-all duration-300
                        ${isRecording ? 'bg-red-500 scale-110 shadow-red-200 shadow-xl' : 'bg-teal-500 shadow-teal-200 shadow-lg'}
                    `}
                >
    { isRecording?<Square className = "text-white w-8 h-8" /> : <Mic className="text-white w-8 h-8" />}
</button>
            ) : (
    <div className= "w-full flex items-center gap-2 bg-white p-3 rounded-xl shadow-sm" >
    <button onClick={ () => new Audio(audioUrl).play() } className = "bg-teal-100 p-2 rounded-full" >
        <Play className="w-5 h-5 text-teal-700" />
            </button>
            < div className = "h-1 bg-stone-200 flex-1 rounded-full overflow-hidden" >
                <div className="h-full w-full bg-teal-500/50" /> {/* Fake progress for MVP */ }
                    </div>
                    < span className = "text-xs font-mono text-stone-400" >00: 42 </span>
                        </div>
            )}

<p className="text-stone-500 font-medium" >
    { isRecording? 'Optager... (Tryk for at stoppe)': audioUrl ? 'Optagelse gemt!' : 'Tryk for at fortælle' }
    </p>
    </div>
    );
};

## Storage Strategy(The Zero - Cost Trick)

Firebase Storage: The free tier gives you 5GB.That is roughly 5,000 minutes of compressed audio.

    Implementation: When they hit "Stop", upload the blob to memories / { circleId } / { questionId }.webm.Save the download URL to the Firestore document.

